# Cyclops Vision

Modular adversarial-robustness fuzzer for vision models. MVP supports Keras (.h5) classifiers, FGSM/PGD attacks, simple transforms (resize/JPEG/blur), metrics (accuracy, ASR, risk score), and Markdown/HTML reporting.

## Quickstart

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .

# Prepare data like examples/imagenet_like/{class0,class1}/image.png

cyclops audit \
  --model ./toy_model.h5 --framework keras --task classify \
  --data ./examples/imagenet_like \
  --attacks fgsm pgd \
  --eps 2/255 4/255 \
  --pgd-steps 10 \
  --transforms "resize=224x224,jpeg=95,blur=0" "resize=224x224,jpeg=80,blur=1" \
  --out ./out/mvp
```

## Architecture (MVP)

- Adapters: `KerasH5Adapter`, `ONNXAdapter (stub)`
- Attacks: `FGSM`, `PGD`
- Transforms: `Resize`, `JPEG`, `Blur`, `Compose`
- Dataset: folder classification loader
- Metrics: accuracy, ASR, risk score
- Reporter: Markdown, HTML
- CLI: `cyclops audit`

## Next steps

- More attacks and EOT
- PyTorch and ONNX gradients
- Object detection adapters and metrics
